title: Vaishnavism - Wikipedia
snippet: According to Bhandarkar, Vaishnavism formed in the Purnaic period through the identification of Vishnu with Narayana and with Vasudeva-Krishna, following his elevation as the "Supreme Spirit".

title: O que é o Vaishnavismo? – ISKCON Brasil
snippet: O Vaishnavismo é uma das principais tradições da cultura espiritual védica ou hindu mais ampla. Ao contrário de algumas tradições védicas, os Vaishnavas acreditam que a realidade última é pessoal. Assim, eles entendem que Deus é a pessoa Suprema e todo-atraente, ou Krishna. title: Vaishnavism | Hinduism’s Most Popular Sect | Britannica
snippet: Vaishnavism, one of the major forms of modern Hinduism, characterized by devotion to the god Vishnu and his incarnations (avatars). A devotee of Vishnu is called a Vaishnava.

title: Vaishnavism - New World Encyclopedia
snippet: Vaishnavism represents one of the largest branches of contemporary Hinduism. Vaishnavism stands out among the other major branches in that it represents the closest continuation of the Vedic tradition, and therefore speaks to the staying power of that ancient system of thought.
